The entrance to the monolithic Shrine of Rveyelhi lies through an arch of
basalt stone to the north.  Breaking an otherwise blank outer curtain wall,
the arch allows access to a small courtyard.  Twin sculptures of a robed,
severe shuddeni, the god\@s avatar of choice, flank the smooth, undecorated
arch.  To the north, a black basalt stair climbs out of a tiny, open yard to
a forbidding edifice crafted from the same dark stone.  Imposing and
monolithic, the square building tapers slightly at the top, but is otherwise
unadorned.  To the south, a spur of Glallia Street wends its way back into
the city.
