#30133
The Hall of the Black Staff~
This open, square hall in the Shrine to Rveyelhi is easily fifteen feet
in height, made from smoothly-polished basalt.  Walls, floor, and ceiling
are all crafted from the same, seamlessly reflective stone, the overall
effect somewhat disorienting though pure and unbroken by anything which
might distract the gaze.  This intersection of halls is lined with
supporting columns, the ceiling ascending in an angular, stepped curve to a
central point high above the floor.  To the east and west the hall narrows
into smaller side rooms, and a hall leads south to the entrance. 
Northwards, a large chamber opens up to house the altar of Rveyelhi.  The
air is very chilly, laden with a thin, alchemical smell.  A definite tension
lingers in the air, a preternatural stillness more reminiscent of stone or
metal than of atmosphere.  
~
